{
  "stem": "14897.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And indications of bad things happening started to happen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And then, of course, some people made it out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The extermination camp where the Jewish-- where the Jews from Warsaw went was called Treblinka, T-R-E-B-L-I-N-K-A, which was just-- I don't know-- a couple hundred miles or less east of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And when they got there, as we later learned, some young healthy men would be picked to actually work temporarily in the camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And the rest of the people would be unloaded and taken to the showers and told to undress and gassed.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And this information filtered back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And when it did, of course, then nobody was willing to go anymore.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So these selections worked in the following way.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "In the morning, the Germans would cordon off some area, some-- a block or something like that of buildings.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And they always did it after the official workers had gone to work, so that the people who were left in those building were already, as we called them, wild, which meant illegal.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And these people were just free pickings for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And so [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my mother and I would stay in those areas.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And in the apartment where we stayed at the time-- and I really don't remember it, it was a different apartment, but I don't remember how we got there-- we had a hiding place.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "In the kitchen-- there was no refrigerator in that apartment, so in the kitchen, the walls were thick.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And under the kitchen window, there was a big cupboard where people used to keep things-- perishables so that they would be exposed colder, cooler kind of, kind of a cooler.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And it had doors and had two shelves.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
